<subSubSection pageId="68" pageNumber="464" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="68.[113,753,285,693]" pageId="68" pageNumber="464">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,224,285,309]" pageId="68" pageNumber="464">Remarks.</emphasis>
So far this is the only genus in the family that has the carapace much broader than long and with the regions distinctly demarcated. As discussed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Huang J-F &amp; Hsueh P-W &amp; Ng PKL" pageId="68" pageNumber="464" pagination="651 - 660" refId="ref45534" refString="Huang J-F, Hsueh P-W &amp; Ng PKL (2002) Crabs of the family Hexapodidae (Decapoda: Brachyura) from Taiwan, with description of a new genus and new species. Journal of Crustacean Biology, 22 (3): 651 - 660." type="journal article" year="2002">Huang et al. (2002)</bibRefCitation>
, the extension of the male thoracic sternal groove is comparable to the condition in 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Alcock" authorityYear="1902" box="[458,624,413,437]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hexapodidae" genus="Lambdophallus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="68" pageNumber="464" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[458,624,413,437]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="464">Lambdophallus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but several differences such as movable eyes (versus immovable eyes in 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Alcock" authorityYear="1902" box="[141,307,477,501]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hexapodidae" genus="Lambdophallus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="68" pageNumber="464" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[141,307,477,501]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="464">Lambdophallus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the shapes of the third maxillipeds with the ischium expanded distally in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huang, Hsueh &amp; Ng" authorityYear="2002" box="[464,600,509,533]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hexapodidae" genus="Latohexapus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="68" pageNumber="464" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[464,600,509,533]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="464">Latohexapus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Huang J-F &amp; Hsueh P-W &amp; Ng PKL" pageId="68" pageNumber="464" pagination="651 - 660" refId="ref45534" refString="Huang J-F, Hsueh P-W &amp; Ng PKL (2002) Crabs of the family Hexapodidae (Decapoda: Brachyura) from Taiwan, with description of a new genus and new species. Journal of Crustacean Biology, 22 (3): 651 - 660." type="journal article" year="2002">Huang et al., 2002</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 4D) (versus slightly convex in 
<taxonomicName authority=", Manning &amp; Holthuis, 1981" authorityName=", Manning &amp; Holthuis" authorityYear="1981" class="Malacostraca" family="Hexapodidae" genus="Lambdophallus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="68" pageNumber="464" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[579,746,541,565]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="464">Lambdophallus</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Manning RB &amp; Holthuis LB" box="[113,397,573,597]" pageId="68" pageNumber="464" pagination="1 - 379" refId="ref45783" refString="Manning RB &amp; Holthuis LB (1981) West African brachyuran crabs (Crustacea: Decapoda). Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology, 306: 1 - 379." type="journal article" year="1981">Manning &amp; Holthuis, 1981</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
: fig. 34b), and the male abdominal somite 6 appearing hexagonal (
<bibRefCitation author="Huang J-F &amp; Hsueh P-W &amp; Ng PKL" box="[451,656,605,629]" pageId="68" pageNumber="464" pagination="651 - 660" refId="ref45534" refString="Huang J-F, Hsueh P-W &amp; Ng PKL (2002) Crabs of the family Hexapodidae (Decapoda: Brachyura) from Taiwan, with description of a new genus and new species. Journal of Crustacean Biology, 22 (3): 651 - 660." type="journal article" year="2002">Huang et al., 2002</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 4G) (versus almost squarish in 
<taxonomicName authority=", Manning &amp; Holthuis, 1981" authorityName=", Manning &amp; Holthuis" authorityYear="1981" class="Malacostraca" family="Hexapodidae" genus="Lambdophallus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="68" pageNumber="464" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[428,601,637,661]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="464">Lambdophallus</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Manning RB &amp; Holthuis LB" pageId="68" pageNumber="464" pagination="1 - 379" refId="ref45783" refString="Manning RB &amp; Holthuis LB (1981) West African brachyuran crabs (Crustacea: Decapoda). Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology, 306: 1 - 379." type="journal article" year="1981">Manning &amp; Holthuis, 1981</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
: fig. 34C) easily distinguishes the two genera.
</paragraph>
